==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yaws
<hw>Yaws</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[African <ets>yaw</ets> a
raspberry.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease, occurring in the
Antilles and in Africa, characterized by yellowish or reddish tumors, of
a contagious character, which, in shape and appearance, often resemble
currants, strawberries, or raspberries. There are several varieties of
this disease, variously known as <stype>framboesia</stype>,
<stype>pian</stype>, <stype>verrugas</stype>, and
<stype>crab-yaws</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yaw-weed</ent>⟦br⟧
